intro:
This isn’t playing war — this is survival.
Pop the case open, pick your weapon, and make it loud. The world won’t save itself — but you can leave your mark.
description:
Every class isn’t just a loadout — it’s attitude, identity, and a challenge thrown in the enemy’s face.
Assault — first in, last one standing.
Sniper — a quiet god who turns heartbeats off with a single click.
Tactical — cuts through silence, breaks plans, owns the moment.
CQB — close enough for the enemy to hear your breath… right before everything goes black.
Anti-Armor — the heavy full stop at the end of any argument.
Mobile — you don’t see him. You just drop.
Breach — if the door doesn’t open, that just means it hasn’t realized it’s gone yet.

Maps shift, situations flip, chaos spreads — but one rule never changes:
If you hesitate for a second, you’re already a memory.

Victory belongs to those who don’t wait for orders, don’t wait for the perfect moment, don’t wait for miracles.
Victory belongs to the one who steps first. And fires.
